-- Japanese Bought Net 26.2 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 2011-12-21T23:59:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/japanese-bought-net-26-2-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Dec. 16 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 26.2 billion yen ($335.6 million)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 60.1 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 29.8 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 63.6 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 278.8 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 210.6 billion yen in stocks, and bought 2661.5 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 2729.8
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  